To insert javascript into out html file we use script tags wrap out code.
We use the language attribute inside the opening script tags
to specify what scripting laguage we will be using.
In this case our value is obviously going to be javascript.

Example:
<script language="javascript">
    javascript code
</script>

Declaring Variable
    var variableName

Functions
    document.write()
        -Displays whatever argument is in the parameter.
    alert()
        -Creates a pop up box displaying whatever argument is in the parameter.
    prompt()
        -Creates a pop up box that takes user input.
        -Displays whatever argument is in the parameter 
         (usually a string message describing the info needed).

Arrays (work pretty much the same as java)
    -Declaring an array
        var myArray = new Array;
    -Adding values to array
        myArray[0]="Rush";
        myArray[1]="Queen";
        myArray[2]="Boston";
    -To return the length of the myArray
        myArray.length
    -To return a value at a specific index in myArray
        myArray[1]
            return value at index 1 of the array
            
It is better to write your javascript in a web editor then link that file
to your html file. 
    -For the first line in the web editor you should type:
        // JavaScript Document
    -Then save the document in the same folder as the html file you wish to
     link the javascript to.
    -After that create the script tags and in the opening tag, add the type
     and src attributes.
        Example:
            <script type="text/javascript" src="filePath"></script>